                <p>&ldquo;I&rsquo;m proud to provide my clients with an appreciation and understanding of the Big Picture in conducting a real estate transaction,&rdquo; Mark says. &ldquo;As a graduate of New York University&rsquo;s Real Estate Institute, I&rsquo;m able to create added value for my residential clients. And as someone who&rsquo;s lived in the area for a long time, I know what a wonderful area this is to call home. I&rsquo;m excited to be able to serve the people who make up these communities.&rdquo;</p>
                <p>The communities Mark serves include Basking Ridge, Bedminster, Bernardsville, Bridgewater, Far Hills, Morristown, Peapack-Gladstone, Stirling and Warren. &ldquo;These towns have school systems that are consistently rated near the top of New Jersey&rsquo;s Public Schools,&rdquo; he explains. &ldquo;Graduates go on to the Ivy&rsquo;s, MIT, Amherst, and many other top universities.&rdquo;</p>
                <p>In addition to the schools, Mark cites as major draws the proximity to commuter transit lines for people who work in Manhattan, as well as the convenience of nearby highways like Routes 287 and 78. And in the bigger picture, he explains that almost anywhere you&rsquo;re looking to buy it&rsquo;s an opportune time to make the move. Rising interest rates and the potential for limits on property tax deductions can seem like challenges to new buyers, but they can also mean sellers are more motivated and eager to work with someone interested in buying.</p>
                <p>Beyond hard data about the area&rsquo;s economy and market trends, Mark&rsquo;s also a trusted resource for people new to the process who want to know what they&rsquo;re about to enter into. He&rsquo;s able to support his clients through each step of the real estate journey, going beyond the closing to make sure they&rsquo;ve gotten precisely what they wanted and needed from the transaction. He&rsquo;s proud to be a true partner to his clients, and places the highest priority on each client&rsquo;s investment.</p>
                <p>You can find Mark on the Berkshire Hathaway site at <a href="http://www.bhhsnj.com/mark.schottenfeld" target="_blank">www.bhhsnj.com/mark.schottenfeld</a>. He can also be reached by phone at (908) 421-1308, or via e-mail at <a href="mailto:mark.schottenfeld@bhhsnj.com">mark.schottenfeld@bhhsnj.com</a>. It&rsquo;s a great time to be looking for your dream home &ndash; let Mark help make those dreams a reality!</p>
